@{fg shine}To install...@{fg text}


Well, @{fg shine}Wallhall@{fg text} can be used either as a normal wall, or as a
replacement for the "@{fg shine}G@{fg text}" command in /X.

@{u}To install it as a logoff-replacement (recomended) :) :@{uu}

Copy The G.INFO file from the Commands/SYSCmd/ path to your matching
path. Then copy all the files in Doors/ to your DOORS:.

Edit the "doors:-mGs!-wALLhALL/wallhall.info" icon to suit your needs:

LINES=<lines>   (Where lines can be anything below 1ooo) This tooltype
                Decides how many tags the users will be able to scan through
                with their cursor-keys. Around 1oo is recommended for speed.

TAGS=<tags>     Is the number of tags the user should be able to enter on the
                wall each time he/she :) logs off. 




@{u}To install it as a "normal" wall (recomended too) :) :@{uu}

Copy The wall.INFO file from the Commands/BBSCmd/ path to your matching
path. Then copy all the files in Doors/ to your DOORS:.

Edit the "doors:-mGs!-wALLhALL/wallhall.info" icon to suit your needs:

LINES=<lines>   (Where lines can be anything below 1ooo) This tooltype
                Decides how many tags the users will be able to scan through
                with their cursor-keys. Around 1oo is recommended for speed.

TAGS=<tags>     Is the number of tags the user should be able to enter on the
                wall each time he/she :) uses the wall. 




@{u}ofcoz you can install it as both :) @{uu}



@endnode





